Neo-Nazis Bet Big on Bitcoin (And Lost)The neo-Nazi terrorist who takes credit for murdering 50 people in Christchurch, New Zealand, on March 15 released a manifesto.
White nationalists were known to be getting into cryptocurrencies during the 2017 bitcoin bubble, because PayPal kept cutting them off.
Yet there were ideological ties, as well as practical considerations, that may have helped push neo-Nazis toward bitcoin.
The neo-Nazis themselves were delighted to embrace May with a laudatory obituary on the white nationalist site the Daily Stormer.
At the peak of the 2017 bitcoin bubble, many worried that neo-Nazis who had bought into bitcoin were now rich and well-resourced.